<item>
            <title>[HBASE-11860] Restore UpgradeTo in order to upgrade a HBase cluster to the latest release</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-11860</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Users should have the option to upgrade to a newer release of HBase without performing a transitive upgrade to HBase 0.96 (EOL&apos;d) or HBase 0.98 and then HBase 1.x or 2.x&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-11611&quot; title=&quot;Clean up ZK-based region assignment&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-11611&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-11611&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; UpgradeTo96 was removed and it won&apos;t be possible to migrate a HBase 0.94 cluster to HBase 1.x or 2.x  without the extra step. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Initially we can restore part of the functionality of the tool supporting migration to namespaces and report for the existence of any HFileV1 file and ZKDataMigrator could be safely removed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
