                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14115266" author="busbey" created="Fri, 29 Aug 2014 14:10:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is your proposal that we adopt a position of always being able to upgrade to a released version from any supported version at the time of release?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;e.g. when presumably when 1.0 comes out 0.94 and 0.98 will still be around and you&apos;d like users to be able to go directly to 1.0 from either (and rolling from 0.98?). Similarly current 0.94 users would be able to go directly to 0.98?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is there already a dev@ discussion around this? Since our &lt;a href=&quot;http://hbase.apache.org/book.html#upgrading&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;upgrade docs&lt;/a&gt; expressly call out not supporting this kind of upgrades it&apos;s probably worth preemptively asking for concerns from the wider audience there.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14115379" author="stack" created="Fri, 29 Aug 2014 16:09:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;First off, what Sean says &quot;...our upgrade docs expressly call out not supporting this kind of upgrades....&quot;  That said, it seems going 0.94 to 1.0 wouldn&apos;t take much work.  If it is just a case of leaving around some deprecated APIs and restoring old scripts removed in zeal, I&apos;d be game for testing and making sure it basically works.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14115420" author="esteban" created="Fri, 29 Aug 2014 16:33:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=busbey&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;busbey&quot;&gt;Sean Busbey&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Is your proposal that we adopt a position of always being able to upgrade to a released version from any supported version at the time of release?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Not across all versions but at least the set of versions actively in use.  I&apos;ve seen that HBase production clusters life is around 2 years with the same version and sometimes do major upgrades skipping a couple of intermediate versions, e.g 0.20 -&amp;gt; 0.94, 0.90 -&amp;gt; 0.94, 0.94 -&amp;gt; 0.98. At least we should support upgrades from previous releases to HBase 1.x.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since our upgrade docs expressly call out not supporting this kind of upgrades....&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think if we have the functionality to migrate a cluster from 0.90 to 0.98 then we should carry that functionality at least to HBase 1.x.  Since 0.96 has been EOL&apos;d I think it should be fine to keep that functionality a little longer. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stack&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stack&quot;&gt;stack&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First off, what Sean says &quot;...our upgrade docs expressly call out not supporting this kind of upgrades....&quot; That said, it seems going 0.94 to 1.0 wouldn&apos;t take much work. If it is just a case of leaving around some deprecated APIs and restoring old scripts removed in zeal, I&apos;d be game for testing and making sure it basically works.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thats right, basically the old UpgradeTo96 &quot;works&quot; and it could be required that the upgrade should be done first to use the old ZK based assignment so existing znodes could be migrated, then users can opt to use the zk-less assignment. If using the zk-less assignment we only need to migrate the HBase filesystem to the new layout.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;P.S. +1 I think we can bring this discussion into the dev@ mailing list. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14126290" author="enis" created="Mon, 8 Sep 2014 23:22:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For the record, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-11611&quot; title=&quot;Clean up ZK-based region assignment&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-11611&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-11611&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is not committed to branch-1 because we still want to support 0.94 -&amp;gt; 1.0 upgrade (though it is still to be tested, see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-11915&quot; title=&quot;Document and test 0.94 -&amp;gt; 1.0.0 update&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-11915&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-11915&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
